<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,756,1153,1723]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">
Saussure (1860) placed this name in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Brandt, 1839" authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,389,1282,1307]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Paradesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis box="[151,239,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">P. klugii</emphasis>
Brandt, 1839
</taxonomicName>
. He stated that the latter species is abundant and that he collected it “à Cordova, à Orizaba, à Panuco et sur tout le versant oriental du plateau”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman R. L." bookContentInfo="584 pp." journalOrPublisher="Virginia Museum of Natural History, Martinsville" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" refString="Hoffman R. L. 1999. Checklist of the millipeds of North and Middle America. Special Publication No. 8. Virginia Museum of Natural History, Martinsville. 584 pp." title="Checklist of the millipeds of North and Middle America. Special Publication No. 8" type="book" year="1999">Hoffman (1999: 389)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously assumed that the localities given by Saussure for the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1839" box="[541,631,1410,1434]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Paradesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis box="[541,631,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">P. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humbert" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,248,1443,1466]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Paradesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picteti">
<emphasis box="[151,248,1443,1466]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">P. picteti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas Saussure (1860: 294) implied that a single ♀ specimen served for the original description. The MHNG collection contains 14 card-mounted specimens under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brandt" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[331,516,1538,1561]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Pachyurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis box="[331,516,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">Pachyurus klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No specimen can be identified as the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humbert" authorityYear="1865" box="[406,499,1571,1594]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Paradesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picteti">
<emphasis box="[406,499,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">P. picteti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the labels, but one fits the size given in the original description and most of the characters described by Saussure (1860: 295), and it may be the holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
